137
00:08:54.634 --> 00:08:55.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ms. Shimomura...

138
00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:59.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
is really hot, isn't she?

139
00:09:00.840 --> 00:09:02.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You think she's with Tosaki?

140
00:09:02.942 --> 00:09:04.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're always together.

141
00:09:04.176 --> 00:09:07.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, I don't think so.
I mean, she's an Ajin after all.

142
00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:09.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What?!
-You mean you didn't notice?

143
00:09:11.017 --> 00:09:13.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She summoned a ghost in the hospital,
right?

144
00:09:13.819 --> 00:09:15.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And when we escaped the village...

145
00:09:15.788 --> 00:09:18.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I wonder if she's got a boyfriend...
-[sighs]

146
00:09:18.224 --> 00:09:19.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

147
00:09:20.927 --> 00:09:22.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on, hurry up.

148
00:09:23.195 --> 00:09:25.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door opens, then closes]

149
00:09:28.568 --> 00:09:30.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh...
-Who's this?

150
00:09:30.703 --> 00:09:32.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ikuya Ogura.

151
00:09:33.606 --> 00:09:35.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He does Ajin research in America.

152
00:09:35.641 --> 00:09:36.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And a genius.

153
00:09:39.912 --> 00:09:42.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're Kei Nagai.

154
00:09:42.682 --> 00:09:44.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The third Ajin found in Japan.

155
00:09:44.984 --> 00:09:46.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Nakano.

156
00:09:46.185 --> 00:09:47.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ajin are fascinating.

157
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:53.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They somehow give a hint of worth
to our meaningless lives.

158
00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:56.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'm Nakano--
-Mind if I smoke?

159
00:09:56.629 --> 00:09:59.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Actually, cigarettes bother me.

160
00:10:04.804 --> 00:10:06.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[coughing]
-[Ogura] Nagai.

161
00:10:07.173 --> 00:10:10.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why do you think it is
that people eventually die?

162
00:10:10.776 --> 00:10:12.812  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because their hearts stop?

163
00:10:14.680 --> 00:10:17.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a limit to the number of times
their cells can regenerate.

164
00:10:17.783 --> 00:10:22.054  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Once you go over that limit, regeneration
stops, and then life functions cease--

165
00:10:22.221 --> 00:10:25.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. It's because
that's what the universe decided.

166
00:10:27.193 --> 00:10:30.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Ogura, let's stay on topic.</i>
<i>Get to the point.</i>

167
00:10:31.130 --> 00:10:35.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>According to "Tazaki"</i>
<i>on the other side of that camera there,</i>

168
00:10:35.768 --> 00:10:37.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>you've got a rather odd IBM.</i>

169
00:10:37.903 --> 00:10:39.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's Tosaki.

170
00:10:39.872 --> 00:10:41.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let's see it.
-What?

171
00:10:41.340 --> 00:10:42.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?!

172
00:10:42.975 --> 00:10:44.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It might kill you.

173
00:10:44.810 --> 00:10:47.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You sound like
a cigarette packaging warning.

174
00:10:47.346 --> 00:10:49.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure, doctor?

175
00:10:49.081 --> 00:10:50.650  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Of course not!
-Settle down.

176
00:10:50.950 --> 00:10:53.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How else can I make a proper diagnosis?

177
00:10:54.920 --> 00:10:56.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you won't be able to see it.

178
00:10:56.956 --> 00:11:00.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll see it if you come at me
like you're going to kill me.

179
00:11:14.440 --> 00:11:18.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The shape is plain, the density is high.

180
00:11:18.811 --> 00:11:21.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's remarkable
that it's so clearly visible.

181
00:11:21.447 --> 00:11:24.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[IBM]
This place is like a sweatshop...

182
00:11:24.717 --> 00:11:26.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I really gotta piss.
-Speak.

183
00:11:27.920 --> 00:11:29.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ogura] Just like in the report.

184
00:11:30.122 --> 00:11:32.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It does the opposite of what
it's ordered to do.

185
00:11:33.459 --> 00:11:36.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Seems twisted, through-and-through.
-[laughs]

186
00:11:39.832 --> 00:11:40.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why me...?

187
00:11:41.767 --> 00:11:44.970  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it goes on autopilot
if it has no orders.

188
00:11:45.271 --> 00:11:47.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This really is fascinating.

189
00:11:47.873 --> 00:11:49.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

190
00:11:50.076 --> 00:11:55.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I saw a similar example from another Ajin,
a farmer who lived in Iowa.

191
00:11:56.982 --> 00:12:02.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>At first, he had the IBM weeding,</i>
<i>and doing simple work like that.</i>

192
00:12:02.988 --> 00:12:05.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But then one morning a few years later,</i>

193
00:12:06.926 --> 00:12:10.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>it just spontaneously</i>
<i>started up the corn harvester.</i>

194
00:12:10.496 --> 00:12:12.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It was actually riding on the tractor.</i>

195
00:12:13.899 --> 00:12:16.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd say yours has been left alone
for too long.

196
00:12:16.869 --> 00:12:21.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Except the first time
that I used it was only a month ago.

197
00:12:21.273 --> 00:12:24.009  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Ogura]
I don't think so. You've had it longer.

198
00:12:24.176 --> 00:12:26.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Probably since you were a little kid.

199
00:12:29.315 --> 00:12:30.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nakano] Watch out!!!

200
00:12:35.321 --> 00:12:36.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How should I handle this?

201
00:12:37.223 --> 00:12:40.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just leave it.
It'll be gone in five minutes.

202
00:12:40.126 --> 00:12:42.061  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Huh?
-[Ogura] What?

203
00:12:42.328 --> 00:12:47.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just when I was experimenting before,
I kept it out for 30 minutes once.

204
00:12:49.301 --> 00:12:51.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How many could you summon in a row?

205
00:12:51.337 --> 00:12:53.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Shimomura] The report says five.

206
00:12:54.039 --> 00:12:55.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Nagai] My personal record is nine.

207
00:12:56.876 --> 00:12:57.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs]

208
00:12:58.043 --> 00:13:02.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's unusual.
And the IBM is abnormally dense.

209
00:13:02.448 --> 00:13:04.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The ghost is... dense?

210
00:13:07.086 --> 00:13:09.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why is there so much?

211
00:13:15.227 --> 00:13:17.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually,
Sato said something like that, too.

212
00:13:18.030 --> 00:13:19.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Nagai! Look at my shirt!

213
00:13:20.332 --> 00:13:22.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You're a blue-collar guy, aren't you?
-This is red!

214
00:13:23.235 --> 00:13:28.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This level of density would only be
possible given a very long time frame...

215
00:13:33.345 --> 00:13:36.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No,
it couldn't just be the length of time...

216
00:13:36.382 --> 00:13:38.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The density of IBMs also change

217
00:13:38.884 --> 00:13:41.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
based on the developmental stage
of the mind and ego...

218
00:13:46.592 --> 00:13:50.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How long have you actually been an Ajin?

219
00:13:50.963 --> 00:13:51.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

220
00:14:00.039 --> 00:14:02.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like I said, it's been about a month.

221
00:14:06.278 --> 00:14:07.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] Just a moment please.

222
00:14:18.290 --> 00:14:19.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you for waiting.

223
00:14:19.925 --> 00:14:22.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Boarding begins 30 minutes before takeoff.

224
00:14:22.261 --> 00:14:23.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have a pleasant trip.

225
00:14:24.029 --> 00:14:26.866  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm going to have a great time.

226
00:14:30.870 --> 00:14:31.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] All clear.

227
00:14:47.119 --> 00:14:49.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[IBM] Here... you... go...

228
00:14:49.588 --> 00:14:50.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

229
00:14:51.257 --> 00:14:55.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're... wel... wal... welcome.

230
00:14:56.061 --> 00:15:01.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For such a talented guy, you certainly
have a hard time using your ghost.

231
00:15:01.500 --> 00:15:06.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's harb... harder to use th...
than machines.

232
00:15:06.238 --> 00:15:09.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, everything takes practice.

233
00:15:09.174 --> 00:15:11.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Simo... Häyhä.

234
00:15:12.077 --> 00:15:14.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's the Okuyama I know.

235
00:15:15.014 --> 00:15:17.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... I'm off.

236
00:15:23.055 --> 00:15:25.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 1]
We get to Miyakojima on the second day.

237
00:15:25.157 --> 00:15:26.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 2]
I bet there'll be some hotties there.

238
00:15:27.126 --> 00:15:28.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 3] Oh, man... I'm getting nervous.

239
00:15:29.028 --> 00:15:32.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman] Already? I told you,
my father's a nice guy. You'll be fine.

240
00:15:33.065 --> 00:15:35.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hope there's no terrorist attacks
or anything.

241
00:15:35.134 --> 00:15:38.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Forget about terrorists.
Let's have a look at the documents.

242
00:15:39.004 --> 00:15:41.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[man 4] Hey,
did you see that guy up in first class?

243
00:15:41.941 --> 00:15:45.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are they escorting
a prisoner or something?

244
00:15:45.144 --> 00:15:46.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man 5] Huh?

245
00:15:46.145 --> 00:15:49.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They wouldn't transport a prisoner
in first class.

246
00:15:53.052 --> 00:15:54.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jesus, relax, would you?

247
00:15:56.522 --> 00:15:58.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All the passengers
have had their IDs checked.

248
00:15:59.658 --> 00:16:01.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Isn't that right?
-Yes, sir.

249
00:16:02.494 --> 00:16:06.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And they wouldn't follow us
out to Okinawa, anyway. [chuckles]

250
00:16:07.132 --> 00:16:11.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even if they show up, we'll just grab them
and throw them in the lab.

251
00:16:11.070 --> 00:16:12.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Sakurai, please watch what you say.

252
00:16:13.172 --> 00:16:15.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[laughs]

253
00:16:16.208 --> 00:16:18.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[stewardess] 
We will be taking off shortly.

254
00:16:41.200 --> 00:16:42.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Sato] Oh...

255
00:16:46.739 --> 00:16:48.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well then.

256
00:16:51.744 --> 00:16:54.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sir, the fasten seatbelt sign
is still...

257
00:16:59.518 --> 00:17:00.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[speaks in Japanese]

258
00:17:01.053 --> 00:17:02.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where's Sakurai?

259
00:17:06.125 --> 00:17:07.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me, sir?

260
00:17:12.431 --> 00:17:13.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasping]

261
00:17:15.367 --> 00:17:16.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

262
00:17:22.107 --> 00:17:24.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[air whistling]

263
00:17:25.144 --> 00:17:26.111  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[stewardess screams]

264
00:17:31.383 --> 00:17:33.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's going on?! [gasps]

265
00:17:38.190 --> 00:17:39.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sato...

266
00:17:40.225 --> 00:17:42.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, there you are.

267
00:17:42.494 --> 00:17:44.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You just went to the bathroom.

268
00:17:46.265 --> 00:17:47.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

269
00:17:47.332 --> 00:17:49.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting and grunting]

270
00:17:52.137 --> 00:17:53.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

271
00:17:53.806 --> 00:17:55.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

272
00:17:59.745 --> 00:18:01.580  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[punch thuds]

273
00:18:01.647 --> 00:18:03.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man whimpering]

274
00:18:12.458 --> 00:18:14.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bon voyage.

275
00:18:32.744 --> 00:18:37.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Nagai] <i>So I can summon more IBMs</i>
<i>than Sato and his crew...</i>

276
00:18:38.851 --> 00:18:41.286  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I may be able to use that</i>
